      "writtenOn": "2019-03-12T00:07:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I recommend doing inline member initialization for any primitive types that won\u0027t default-initialize (instead of doing it in the constructor).\n\nFor example, this could be:\nbool mMacroPlaying \u003d false;\nMacroUiState mState \u003d MacroUiState::Waiting;\n\nThe other fields, like std::string and std::unique_ptr have default constructors, so they don\u0027t need to be explicitly initialized.\n\nThe benefit is that doing it here guarantees it is set, it\u0027s easy to make a mistake and forget the constructor.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 46,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 46,
        "endChar": 23
      },
